<HEADLINE> Eritrea's Army Soldiers in Ethiopia Detained </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The spokesperson of the
Ethiopian government announced Saturday that the Ethiopian
government has arrested for security reasons the Eritrean
government soldiers residing in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted the spokesperson as saying,
''The amry members who came to Ethiopia before Eritrean's
invasion were put under custody to maintain national security,''
reported the Ethiopian News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The spokesperson did not give the number of the Eritrean army
soldiers who are residing in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The spokesperson said, ''The individuals could be threat to
national security.'' The measure will not apply to Eritreans
leading a peaceful life in Ethiopia, he added.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the number of Eritreans residing in Ethiopia, the
spokesperson denied the number is over 550,000 announced here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the announcement made by a government
spokesperson here Friday, the Ethiopian government policy toward
Eritreans living in Ethiopia ''remains intact'' and the Eritreans
can "continue to live and work peacefully in Ethiopia." But the
spokesperson said that the Eritreans "who are in leadership
positions in security sensitive posts - such as
telecommunications and the electricity company - must take one
month's enforced leave."  
</P>
</TEXT>
