<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Launches Measles Vaccination Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The national measles vaccination
campaign in Zimbabwe is estimated to have reached over 80 percent
of the targeted children aged from nine months to 14 years,
according to Health and Child Welfare Minister Timothy Stamps.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Zimbabwe News Agency at the weekend,
the minister said despite the fears that the program would not
manage to cater for all the people, it had been very effective
with more children being immunized.
</P>
<P>
Because of the successful drive which ends Sunday, Stamps
said, the country would reduce the risk of measles infection.
</P>
<P>
The 14-day national immunization program has been launched by
the government to fight measles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
