<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Marked Growth Of Industrial Production In Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The industrial sector in east
China's Shandong Province recorded 52.06 billion yuan in sales in
May, 710 million yuan higher than the figure in April, with the
production-to-sales ratio rising 0.4 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
Local industrial enterprises with annual sales beyond five
million yuan each had more than 15.4 billion yuan in added
value last month, up 14.7 percent over the previous month.
</P>
<P>
During the January-May period of this year, the province
recorded 71.27 billion yuan in industrial added value, a 10.2
percent rise from the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Added value achieved by local state industrial enterprises rose
five percent from April to reach nearly 6.58 billion yuan in May;
that of non-state businesses rose nearly 22 percent to hit 8.89
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The province ranked third in China with 665 billion yuan of GDP
in 1997, which is expected to grow at a rate of nine percent this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
