<HEADLINE> Zambia Saddened by Situation in Guinea Bissau </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government is saddened
by latest developments in Guinea Bissau where rebels led by the
sacked armed forces commander, Ansumane Mane, are seeking to
topple the elected government.
</P>
<P>
David Mpamba, Zambian Minister of Information and Broadcasting
Services and Chief government spokesman, Sunday described the
rebels in the tiny west African country as a "disgrace to
Africa".
</P>
<P>
The Zambia News Agency (ZANA) Sunday quoted Mpamba as saying
that the people of Guinea Bissau are now being subjected to
suffering and displacements because of selfishness, greed and
lust for power by a few disgruntled elements in the country.
</P>
<P>
The minister urged the Organization of African Unity (OAU) and
all peace-loving people worldwide to condemn the rebellion in
Guinea Bissau.
</P>
<P>
He called on Africans to fight for the elimination of
injustices among the people and the uplifting of people's living
standards.
</P>
<P>
Heavy shelling has been reported since last Friday in Guinea
Bissau where rebels led by Brigadier Mane is seeking to topple
the government of President Joao Bernardo Vieira.
</P>
<P>
The rebellion broke out after Mane was fired by President
Vieira six days ago for alleged negligence in the case of army
officers accused of smuggling arms to rebels in the southern
Senegalese province of Casamance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
