<HEADLINE> Del Piero Slams Italian TV Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Alessandro Del Piero criticized Italian
television coverage on Sunday for alleged insinuation that he was
unhappy with Roberto Baggio's equalizer against Chile.
</P>
<P>
The Junventus striker, who sit out the Thursday's match on bench,
was infuriated by images broadcasted on the Italian televison which
suggested he was nonchalant when Baggio converted the spot kick.
</P>
<P>
"I was very much disappointed with the way some of the media, not
the written media, covered the way I reacted to Baggio's penalty," Del
Piero told a news conference at Italy's training base in Senlis, about
50 kilometers north of Paris.
</P>
<P>
"It seemed to me excessive," Del Piero said, adding that the
televsion only showed shots of him four minutes after the goal.
</P>
<P>
"They suggested I wasn't celebrating. But what am I supposed to do,
keep my arms in the air until the end of the match? People who were
sitting with me saw how I reacted to the goal. I was as pleased as
anyone," he said.
</P>
<P>
Del Piero was nursing an injury prior to the game and his place in
the midfield was hence occupied by Baggio. 
</P>
