<HEADLINE> China Promotes Model Workers In Re-employment Programs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Senior Communist Party of China
(CPC) official Wei Jianxing met here today with representatives of
former laid-off workers who have made achievements in their new
jobs, and called on workers in all state enterprises across the
country to follow their example.
</P>
<P>
Wei, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau
of CPC Central Committee, said that it is a trying experience for
most workers to accept the fact of being laid-off, find themselves
a new job and cope with problems in their new employment.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the success and achievements of the workers
in the re-employment programs testify to the fact that they can
overcome difficulties and establish themselves in new work
positions with the help of the government and the support of
society as a whole, as long as they acquire a sound understanding
of the market economy and are willing to take their chances.
</P>
<P>
Wei urged publicity departments at all levels to promote these
model workers so as to facilitate the working of the re-employment
program and help state enterprise reforms as well.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Publicity Department of the CPC Central
Committee and the All-China Federation of Trade Unions, these
representatives of former laid-off workers have lectured across
the country since mid-May. Their stories and experiences have
inspired other workers to take up challenges and opportunities in
the course of state enterprise reform. 
</P>
</TEXT>
