<HEADLINE> Argentina Score Hard-Fought Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
TOULOUSE, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Gabriel Batistuta gave twice World
Cup winners Argentina a hard-fought 1-0 over World Cup newcomers Japan
in a Group H match here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Batistuta, the ace striker of Argentina, took advantage of
Japanese defender's error to beat the goal-keeper with a volley shot
at the 28th minute.
</P>
<P>
Before the match, the Japanese coach Takeshi Okada said his team
had the ability to beat Argentia. The 25 minutes of play seemed to
prove his prediction.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese team surprised their opponents with a fast passing
game and dominated the midfield thanks to their Asian Player of the
Year Hidetoshi Nakata.
</P>
<P>
But the experienced Argentine team soon fought back and forced
their first corner at the 26th minute.
</P>
<P>
The high-spirited Japanese refused to back off and the Argentine
team took the chance to launch quick counter-attacks.
</P>
<P>
At the 28th minute, an Argentine attack caused a chao in front
of the Japanese goal. The Japanese defenders tried to clear the
ball only to see Batistuta picked up the ball within the area and
beat the goal-keeper with an easy volley.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine team had more scoring chances in the first half
but Ariel Ortega squandered them.
</P>
<P>
The second half saw the Argentine team dominate most time of the
playing. But the Japanese players refused to give up and put up
desperate attack in the last ten minutes.
</P>
<P>
Lopez, a second-half substitute, had the best chance to level
the score for Japan at the 88th minute but his shot was blocked by
Argentine defender.
</P>
<P>
Later on Sunday, the other Group H match between Jamaica and
Lens will be played at Lens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
