<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Promoting Environmental Protection Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi Province
had 287 enterprises involved in the environmental protection
industry, with 35,000 employees, 915 million yuan of fixed assets
and nearly four billion yuan of output value in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The environmental protection industry includes environmental
protection equipment manufacturing, construction of environmental
protection facilities and related services.
</P>
<P>
The environmental protection industry appeared first in Shaanxi
in the 1970s. The province's environmental protection enterprises
produce equipment for noise suppression, water treatment and
energy saving.
</P>
<P>
This industry is one of eight major burgeoning industries in
the province, and enjoys a series of preferential policies
regarding funds, technology transfer, market promotion and
taxation.
</P>
<P>
In the coming three to five years, Shaanxi will promote ten
environmental protection enterprises with annual output values of
over 100 million yuan each, 30 with annual output values of over
50 million yuan each and 50 with annual output values of over ten
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi is expected to earn seven billion yuan in total annual
output value from the environmental protection industry by the
year 2000, and 30 billion yuan in total annual output value by the
year 2010. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
