<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floods Threaten Jiangxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 14 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi Province is
facing a threat of flooding, following heavy rain over past couple
of days.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, in 29 cities and counties in the
province over 100 mm of rain fell June 12 and 13. Among them, 10
counties were battered by over 200 mm of rain, bringing the water
level in the Xinjiang River, the main water source of the region,
well above the danger line.
</P>
<P>
By this afternoon, the river water level in Guixi County had
exceeded the danger line by 4.2 m. The provincial hydrometric
station announced that it expected the Xinjiang River to have its
highest water level in history, as the downpour is continuing.
</P>
<P>
So far, no casualties have been reported in the region, and the
provincial government has been mobilizing the local people to be
prepared to fight possible flooding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
