<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Invites Hamas to Join PNA Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) President Yasser Arafat has asked Hamas to discuss the
possibility of joining his cabinet, but Hamas said this matter
has to be decided by its leader Sheikh Ahmed Yassin.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by a PNA official in Gaza on Sunday when
asked by Xinhua to confirm the reports that Arafat has invited
Hamas (Islamic Resistance Movement) to join his cabinet as part
of a cabinet reshuffle.
</P>
<P>
The PNA has forwarded Arafat's request to Hamas officials
in Gaza on Saturday. Arafat wants to meet Hamas leaders as part
of wide-ranging discussions across the Palestinian political
spectrum on forming a new government, the official said.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting of the Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO)
Executive Committee in Gaza on Thursday, Arafat agreed to
reshuffle his cabinet. The decision came days ahead of a June 15
deadline set by the Palestinian Legislative Council (PLC) for
Arafat to reform his administration over alleged corruption and
mismanagement or face a no-confidence vote in the PLC.
</P>
<P>
Arafat asked the PLC Saturday to delay a no-confidence vote for
10 days pending a cabinet reshuffle, which the PLO officials said
could be announced on June 25.
</P>
<P>
Hamas leader in Gaza Mahmoud Zahar said on Saturday that the
movement's spiritual leader Yassin would return to Gaza early
Tuesday and would decide on Arafat's offer after his return.
</P>
<P>
Yassin is visiting Sudan after touring other Arab
nations and is waiting for the permission from Israel for his
return to Gaza.
</P>
<P>
Zahar denied that Hamas will change its political ideology if
it decides to join the PNA ranks.
</P>
<P>
Hamas has rejected previous offers to join the PNA
administration and boycotted Palestinian elections in 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
