<HEADLINE> Qinghua University Honors Chinese-American Physicist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Chen Ning Yang, a Nobel Laureate,
in physics, has been appointed an honorary professor of Qinghua
University, one of the most prestigious universities in China,
today.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Chen Ning Yang, a Chinese-American physicist, was born in
Hefei City, Anhui Province, in 1922. Yang, who graduated from the
subsidiary high school of Qinghua University, won the 1957 Nobel
Prize for physics.
</P>
<P>
Since 1971, he has visited China many times, and was appointed
an honorary director of the research center of Qinghua
University.
</P>
<P>
After today's appointment ceremony, Yang delivered a lecture to
more than 200 faculty members and students of the university.
</P>
