<HEADLINE> Elderly Giant Panda Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, June 14 (Xinhua) -- One of the oldest giant pandas in
China, 31-year-old Zhuzhu, died in the zoo in this capital of
southwest China's Guizhou Province June 8.
</P>
<P>
The cause of death was respiratory tract failure
</P>
<P>
Doctors at the hospital affiliated with the Guiyang Medical
College tried all possible emergency measures to save the life of
the panda, but without success, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
The average life span of the giant panda, a species under top
state protection, is 16 years in the wild and 20 to 25 years in
captivity.
</P>
<P>
The oldest giant panda in China is 36-year-old Dudu in the
zoo in Wuhan, the capital of central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
</TEXT>
