<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10,990 Eritrean Soldiers Killed or Wounded in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia announced Sunday
that 10,990 Eritrean soldiers were killed or wounded in three-day
ground fighting from June 9 to 11.
</P>
<P>
A news release issued here by the office of the Ethiopian
government spokesperson also said that during the three-day
fighting in Badme, Zala Ambesa and Bure, about 150 Eritrean
soldiers were captured and thousands of heavy and light armaments
captured.
</P>
<P>
The news release said that 5,414 Eritrean soldiers were killed
or wounded in the fighting on the Badme front during June 10 and
11, in which troops of Eritrea's 381st and 161st divisions
participated.
</P>
<P>
A total of 4,176 Eritrean soliders were killed or wounded in
the battle on the Zala Ambesa front on June 9.
</P>
<P>
While 1,400 Eritrean soldiers were killed or wounded in the
fighting on the Bure front on June 11, in which Eritrea's Special
Command forces participated, the news release said, the damage to
Ethiopian forces was minimal compared to Eritrea's losses.
</P>
<P>
This is the first announcement from the Ethiopian government
after the three-day ground fighting on three fronts of Badme,
Zala Ambesa and Bure from June 9 to 11.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
