<HEADLINE> Marseille Calm after Skirmishes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MARSEILLE, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The "Soccer-Mad" Marseille was
calm on Sunday after midnight fights between police and hundreds of
English fans.
</P>
<P>
But police were prepared for further skirmishes with up to 10,000
England supporters heading to the port city before England's opening
match against Tunisia on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In the skirmishes, a number of English fans were arrested but it
was not clear if any had been charged.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the fight started when an England supporter
were knocked down by a car. The other English fans pelted other
passing vehicles with bottles and glasses as the injured fan
received medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said one policeman was injured in the skirmishes.
Police also closed cafes and bars in Marseille to prevent
drunkenness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
