<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ronaldo Promises to End Goal Drought During World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian superstar Ronaldo said his
goal drought would end during the World Cup.
</P>
<P>
The ace striker has not scored in Brazil's last four games,
including the World Cup opener between Brazil and Scotland which
Brazil prevailed 2-1.
</P>
<P>
"I'm not worried," said Ronaldo, "This is a very important
moment in my career and it is not going to be in a World Cup that I
am going to fail to score."
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo averaged two goals per three international matches until
the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Before the World Cup, Ronaldo once said he hoped to break the
40-year-old record of 13 goals in a single World Cup set by Frenchman
Just Fontaine.
</P>
<P>
But now he said he was not interested in being the topscorer in
the World Cup. "My main concern is that Brazil win a fifth World
Cup." Ronaldo said.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo has scored 25 goals in 38 internationals. The last time
he scored for Brazil was in the warm-up match against Germany.
</P>
</TEXT>
