<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigerian Referee Set to Be Out of World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian referee who awarded a
penalty kick to Roberto Baggio is set to be out of the World Cup
finals as FIFA thought his performance was unsatisfactory.
</P>
<P>
Lucien Bouchardeau ruled that Chilean defender Ronald Fuentes had
deliberately handled the ball when Baggio flicked it on to his hand.
</P>
<P>
Baggio converted the penalty kick and secured a vital point for
Italy in the match against Chile.
</P>
<P>
A senior member of the referees' committee confirmed:"Bouchardeau
has been given a severe dressing down by the FIFA adjudicators. No
one can believe he gave the penalty. I Would not expect him to
referee any more games."
</P>
<P>
FIFA will give each referee at least one game and then assess
their performances individually before deciding who will referee the
later stages of the first round matches.
</P>
<P>
A FIFA spokesman said:"It's possible that the weaker referees
may get to referee one of the meaningless games in the later stages,
but that's yet to be decided. If we were unhappy with their
performance then they won't referee again." 
</P>
</TEXT>
