<HEADLINE> Senior Iranian Judge Kidnaped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Head of the justice department in
Jiroft of Iran's central province of Kerman, Masoud Amir Mayjani,
has been kidnaped by unidentified armed men, the official news
agency IRNA reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Eye witnesses said that Mayjani was kidnaped Friday night from
his home, according to the IRNA. The kidnapers opened fire on a
group of youth who tried to prevent their escape after they forced
Mayjani into a car.
</P>
<P>
So far no one has claimed responsibility for the
abduction. However, a massive search is underway to locate and
arrest the kidnapers.
</P>
<P>
There is a likelihood that the kidnapers may be relatives of
people who have been sentenced by the judge, the IRNA said.
</P>
