<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany to Face Stronger U.S. Team in Group F </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 14 (Xinhua) -- When European champions Germany meets
the United States in the World Cup finals here on Monday, they would
hear stronger notes amid a Symphony from the New Continent.
</P>
<P>
Germany's assisstant coach Rainer Bonhof said their main threat in
the Group F game would be 24-year-old American Claudio Rayna, the
playmaker who is with German Bundersliga side Vfl Wolsburg.
</P>
<P>
"He is the orchestrator and a key figure. He is the main thinker,"
said Bonhof.
</P>
<P>
He added the Americans, despite their image as underdogs, had
matured since the last World Cup finals when they lost to Brazil in
the second round.
</P>
<P>
"Tactically they are more experienced. Before they had good players
but they tended to work on their own. Now they are more of a team and
they work much better together."
</P>
<P>
German head coach Berti Vogts could not agree more.
</P>
<P>
"The match here have shown that standards at the top of the game
are getting closer and closer. You can't tal about small teams any
more."
</P>
<P>
But first of all, the Germans have to shake off their fame as slow
starters in the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the 1990 finals in Italy where they crushed Yugoslavia
4-1 in the opener, the formidable German chariot is reluctant to
accelerate in the first stage.
</P>
<P>
Since this time they will face a much stronger Yugoslavia again in
their second group game, the clash with the Americans is no doubt
important.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have just met twice before, with Germany winning both
in 1993 friendly series in the United States.
</P>
<P>
American midfielder Cobi Jones, a star of 1994, said he relished
being an underdog and was inspired by teams who had defied the
experts.
</P>
<P>
"You see Scotland come out and do well against Brazil, and Morocco
do so well against Norway and Chile against Italy," Jones said.
</P>
<P>
"These situations, where team were meant to go out and kill other
teams, do not happen. Our time's coming up," he added.
</P>
<P>
American coach Steve Sampson seemed to no longer have to worry
about injuries in the team, with midfielder Frankie Hejduk to be fit
to play a half after recovering from a hamstring problem and striker
Eric Wynalda recuperating from knee surgery in April.
</P>
<P>
Vogts, on the other side, is expected to rest veteran sweeper
Lothar Matthaeus on the bench and field Olaf Thon instead.
</P>
<P>
However, it is not clear up to now whether Vogts will play
experienced midfielder Thomas Haessler, who is thought to be picked
along with Andy Moeller. 
</P>
</TEXT>
