<HEADLINE> Arafat Arrives in Cairo for Talks With Mubarak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority (PNA)
President Yasser Arafat arrived here early Sunday for talks with
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak, the Middle East News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Arafat has postponed the Cairo visit scheduled for Thursday due
to his engagements. He began a two-day official trip to the
Vatican and Italy on Friday and then postponed his visit to
Tunisia until after he makes a brief stop in Cairo.
</P>
<P>
In Cairo, the two leaders will discuss the outcome of Arafat's
recent tour in several Arab countries to lobby support for an Arab
summit meeting to form a unified response to the long-stalled
Palestinian-Israeli peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Arab leaders, responding to Arafat's repeated calls, are
holding intensive contacts over the convocation of such a summit
but still yet to reach agreement on its venue, timing and agenda.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian president said last week that such a gathering
needs good preparation and coordination to ensure its success.
</P>
<P>
Arafat made his case in Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso, last week
when he attended the African Summit. Upon his return to Gaza
Wednesday, he said that "we" are still following up the issue with
Arab heads of state and that contacts are still on with most of
them.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian-Israeli talks broke down in March 1997 when
Israel began work on a new Jewish settlement in Arab East
Jerusalem. Israel has rejected the latest U.S. proposal on an
Israeli second phase redeployment from 13.1 percent of the West
Bank, which Arafat has accepted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
