<HEADLINE> Permadi Wins U.S. Badminton Open Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Taipei's Fung Permadi
won his first men's singles title in two years by beating
Scotland's Bruce Flockhart 15-8, 15-5 in the final of the
U.S. Open badminton tournament in Orange, California on Saturday
night.
</P>
<P>
Permadi, ranked 31st in the world, relied on a short-service
game that kept Flockhart off balance.
</P>
<P>
Scotland's Elinor Middlemiss earned two doubles trophies,
winning the women's doubles with Kirsteen McEwan and the mixed
doubles with her husband, Kenny.
</P>
<P>
Ye Ping Tang of the United States ousted second-seeded Jo
Muggeridge of Britain 7-11, 11-4, 11-3 to win the women's singles
title.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Taipei's Shin-Jeng Horng and Wei-Jen Lee won the men's
doubles crown after defeating 2nd seed Iain Sydie/Darryl Yung,
Canada, 12-15, 15-12, 15-6. 
</P>
