<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pudong's Exports Continue to Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The export value of the Pudong
New Area in this east China metropolis surged 23 percent in the
first five months of this year to reach 1.65 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
However, the figure was lower than the over-30 percent growth
in the first quarter, said an official from the local foreign trade
bureau.
</P>
<P>
Exports of traditional items such as textiles and garments
dropped considerably, while those of mechanical and electrical
products increased sharply.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Asian countries recorded a big reduction compared
with last year's same period, but those to Europe and the United
States rose rapidly.
</P>
<P>
The export volume is expected to keep a rising momentum in
the upcoming months as a result of continued industrial growth and
readjustment of the export structure, the official said.
</P>
<P>
But exports from state-owned foreign trade companies is likely
to decline in the near future owing to the impact of the Asian
financial crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
