<HEADLINE> Zambians to Enjoy Cost-Effective Health Care </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has
introduced the Zambian Package of Health Care (ZPHC) to provide
basic, cost-effective health care as a minimum entitlement to all
Zambians.
</P>
<P>
The package which is being financed by the government and
cooperating partners will target the main causes of disease
burden, the Sunday Mail newspaper quoted Health Minister Nkandu
Luo as saying.
</P>
<P>
"The package has a number of elements but it basically
identifies cost-effective interventions at each level of the
system and being able to target the main causes of disease
burden," said the minister.
</P>
<P>
"The package is being financed through government and
cooperating partners although a gap still exists for its full
implementation," Luo said.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that her ministry is determined to address
all the deficiencies and to ensure that the sector is made more
responsive to the existing and emerging health challenges of
delivering quality health care to the Zambian people.
</P>
<P>
The package will focus on improving public hospitals by
ensuring that linen and drugs are available at all times and that
drugs are procured and supplied efficiently and that staff
attitudes are consistent with the professional demands and ethics
of their work, she said.
</P>
<P>
Luo said that the package will, among other things,
concentrate on infrastructure development through construction,
rehabilitation and upgrading of 400 health units in the country.
</P>
<P>
Beds and linen will be secured in public hospitals and drug
kits for rural health centers will be supplied in accordance with
the package, said the minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
