<HEADLINE> China's Steel Imports to Surge This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 14 (Xinhua) -- China is expected to raise steel
imports this year due to a massive investment plan launched by
the Chinese government, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Although steel imports have remained stagnant so far this year,
the rapid development of industries like construction, electrical
appliances and ship-building will strongly boost domestic demand
for steel products, said Meng Guirong, president of the China
Chamber of Commerce for Metals, Minerals and Chemicals Importers
and Exporters(CCCMC).
</P>
<P>
As much as 750 billion US dollars in investment will be
injected into infrastructure projects within the next three years,
and the real estate industry has been chosen by the central
government as one of the major growth points of the national
economy.
</P>
<P>
The on-going reform of the welfare housing system will further
ginger up the construction industry, and hence the demand for steel
products.
</P>
<P>
A considerable proportion of the market demand will come from
imports, due to a mismatch between types of steel products demanded
by the market and those supplied by domestic manufacturers, Meng
said.
</P>
<P>
He forecast this year's total steel import will surpass 10
million tons, though the figure may be smaller than last year's
13.23 million tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
