<HEADLINE> Utah Edge Washington 78-77 in WNBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Kim Williams' layup with nine
seconds left completed a late comeback as the Utah Starzz pulled
out at 78-77 victory over the expansion Washington Mystics on the
winner's home floor on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Tammi Reiss and elena Baranova scored 17 points apiece for the
Starzz, who evened their record at 1-1 after dropping their opener
to Los Angeles. Williams scored the final five points of the game
to finish with 10.
</P>
<P>
Nikki McCray scored 26 points for the Mystics, who have lost
two games in a row. They blew a chance for their first win by
turning the ball over on the their final two possessions. 
</P>
