<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norwood Retains WBA Featherweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Freddy Norwood retained his WBA
featherweight title when he knocked down Genaro Rios of Nicaragua
in the eighth round at in Atlantic City of the United States on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Norwood, who improved his record to 30-0-1 with 19 knockouts,
floored the WBA's number one contender twice early in the fight
that was scheduled for 12 rounds.
</P>
<P>
"That kid was a good fighter, but I can't touched when I'm at
my best," Norwood said. "I was surprised he made it out of the
second round, but I wasn't in any hurry. It's just a matter of
time before I do it again."
</P>
<P>
Norwood hit Rios with a left uppercut in the eighth round.
Rios stumbled and prompted referee to stop the fight.
</P>
<P>
Norwood would like to unify the featherweight division by
adding the WBC and IBF belts, but said he would relish the chance
to first fight England's Prince Naseem Hamed, the flamboyant WBO
champion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
