<HEADLINE> Comets Beats Liberty in WNBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Sheryl Swoopes scored a
career-high 28 points to lead the Houston Comets to a 73-62
victory over the New York Liberty on Saturday in a rematch of the
inaugural WNBA championship game in Houston.
</P>
<P>
Swoopes, who played only nine regular seaon games last year
after returning from childbirth, showed speed and agility, joining
hands with Cynthia Cooper to hit 24 of the Comets' first 25
points. The two players, the league's MVP last season, shot in 46
points at halftime.
</P>
<P>
New York won the first three regular-season games with the
Comets, but the Comets won the final regular-season game and beat
the Liberty 65-51 in the title game. 
</P>
