<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Sends Supplies Into Albania for Kosovo Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. High Commissioner for
Refugees (UNHCR) on Saturday sent the first batch of relief
supplies into the Rinas airport of Tirana, in a bid to help
displaced Kosovo Albanian refugees.
</P>
<P>
The first 10 tons of supplies of foods, blankets, kitchen
utensils and tents were rolled off a C-130 Hercules on loan from
NATO.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR officials here said a total of 150 tons of aid will be
airlifted into Albania in four days from now on.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a total of 22 tons of material, provided by France,
were also sent into Albania.
</P>
<P>
Since early June, the crisis in the troubled Serbian province
of Kosovo has already sent 15,000 ethnic Albanians into the
impoverished northern part of Albania, according to UNHCR
estimates.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government, already plagued by the difficult
economic situation, could not afford the burden of the sudden
influx of refugees. It called on the international community to
provide emergency humanitarian aid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
