<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Be Brought Under TB Control Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's all the 460
sub-districts will be brought under a tuberculosis control program
this month, press reports said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
This was stated by State Minister for Health and Family Welfare
M. Amaullah Khan while addressing a seminar on tuberculosis and
leprosy diseases here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Eighty-two percent of the country's total population of 127
million had already been brought under TB treatment facility, he
said.
</P>
<P>
About 80,468 patients were cured by treatment by last December
and more than 13,000 patients were under treatment under the TB
control program, he told the seminar.
</P>
<P>
The state minister urged physicians, health workers and social
workers to work together to control TB and leprosy.
</P>
<P>
Tuberculosis is frequently-occurring disease in sub-tropical
Bangladesh, and the government has succeeded in controlling its
spread in the country due to a series of measures undertaken with
assistance of the World Health Organization (WHO). 
</P>
</TEXT>
