<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rural Areas Need More TVs and Fridges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Rural China with a population of
nearly 900 million is a huge potential market waiting for
electrical appliance producers to arrive, today's China Daily
quoted an industry official as saying.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Feng, deputy secretary-general of China Household
Electrical Appliances Association, said that China's burgeoning
electrical appliance industry should focus on developing rural
markets as urban consumption stagnates.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent investigation conducted by the State
Information Center, household electrical appliances account for
38.64 percent of rural household spending in the first half this
year.
</P>
<P>
The rural demand focuses on color TVs, refrigerators and
washing machines, the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, China's rural areas had 20.54 washing
machines, 7,27 refrigerators and 22.91 color TVs per hundred
households in 1996.
</P>
<P>
"Traditional appliances will still be the rural household's top
choice in the coming years due to the current low saturation
level," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
But many farmers still can not afford the current prices of
household appliances, despite recent price plunges, he added.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that domestic producers should develop a series of
low-cost products suitable to the rural market.
</P>
<P>
The State Information Center's report indicated that 31.38
percent of sample rural households plan to buy TV sets this year,
with 23,22 percent want washing machines and 19.46 percent favor
refrigerators. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
