<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Chatumongol Sonakul, governor of Thailand's central
bank, has said the baht remained relatively stable with no signs
of speculative activity despite the week-long continued fall of
the Japanese yen against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The yen reached an eight-year low last Friday, testing 145 to
the dollar before strengthening late in the day to end at 144.5.
(Thailand-Currency)
</P>
<P>
-- --
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Japan has agreed in principle to loan Laos 36.5
million U.S. dollars to construct a second Mekong River bridge
linking the land-locked country to neighboring Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Japan is expected to approve the loan next month, and the
construction of the bridge should begin at the end of 2000,
according to a report from the official Lao press.
(Laos-Japan-Loan)
