bilateral cooperation in the fields of industry and investment,
the Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The protocol, signed by the head of the Egyptian Industries
Federation, Abdel Monem Saudi, and the Iranian chief of Mining,
Trade and Industry Federation, Ali Khamoush, aims to increase and
develop trade exchange as well as bilateral cooperation in
industrial and investment spheres. (Egypt-Iran-Trade Team)
</P>
<P>
-- --
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- The price of the Venezuelan basket of crudes and
byproducts for export dropped 0.52 U.S. dollars a barrel during
the last week, down to 10.2 dollars a barrel.
</P>
<P>
The basket of seven crudes exported by the Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) lost 92 cents, closing the
same week at 11.82 dollars per barrel, according to figures
released by the Energy and Mines Ministry. (Venezuela-Oil Prices)
</P>
<P>
-- --
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian Minister of Industries Gholamreza Shafei on
Saturday called for new foreign investment in order to
reinvigorate the country's ailing economy.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening session of the Iran-Austria Joint
Economic Commission, Shafei said Iran welcomes new foreign
investment in its industries in order to realize its main goal of
gaining a bigger share in the world trade. (Iran-Foreign
Investment-Appeal) 
</P>
