<HEADLINE> Albania, Macedonia Expand Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Albania and the Republic of
Macedonia signed an agreement here Saturday to expand their
economic cooperation into all fields.
</P>
<P>
Under the protocol, signed by Albanian Prime Minister Fatos
Nano and his Macedonian counterpart Branko Crvenkovski, the two
countries will strengthen long-term economic cooperation in such
areas as infrastructure, road transportation, telecommunication,
energy and minerals.
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference, Nano said the signing of the
protocol will contribute to the creation of a unified market in
the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
Crvenkovski arrived here on Saturday for a two-day visit.
</P>
</TEXT>
