<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Govt to Set Up Foreign Relations Unit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, 14 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has decided
to set up a Foreign Relations Unit (FRU) in the Ministry of
Cultural and Religious Affairs (MCRA), according to MCRA sources
here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The primary objectives of the new unit will revive and
strengthen cultural relations and mutual understanding between Sri
Lanka and other countries, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the objectives, they said, the unit will initiate
activities and actions to establish cultural agreements with other
foreign countries, establish Sri Lankan cultural centers in
countries of importance, and promote cultural relations especially
with the South Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the sources added that the unit will establish
more meaningful cultural relations with foreign countries, and
programs in association with the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and
Tourist Board to promote cultural tourism in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
