<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Invite Bids for Transformers for Three Gorges Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 14 (Xinhua) --The Three Gorges Project developer
will invite bids from domestic and foreign firms for transformers
and other equipment to be used by the project late this year or at
the beginning of next year, "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The new tender will include fifteen 500-kilovolt transformers,
gas-insulated switching gear, and other equipment to be used in
the left-bank powerhouse of the project, the newspaper quoted
Zhang Geng, General Manager of the Three Gorgers International
Tendering Company (TGT), as saying.
</P>
<P>
TGT is a subsidiary of the China Yangtze Three Gorges Project
Development Corp., the developer of the gigantic Three Gorges
water control dam that will be built on the middle reaches of the
Yangtze River in central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
While observing the principle of "open bidding, fair
competition and honest evaluation" , TGT will give priority to
domestic products if their quality can fully satisfy the demands
of the project. But some key appliances, including large
transformers, will be purchased form international bidders.
</P>
<P>
The general manager stressed that international commercial
loans and export credit will remain indispensable for the
international bidders to win the contract, and foreign government
loans will be especially welcome.
</P>
<P>
It will also be necessary for foreign bidders to pass on their
top technologies to Chinese counterparts as part of the process,
said Zhang.
</P>
<P>
Many foreign firms have already expressed interest in the
bidding, and the developer has conducted technical discussions
with some of them.
</P>
<P>
TGT is also ready to launch bidding for monitoring and control
equipment for the left-bank powerhouse next year, according to the
general manager.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
