<HEADLINE> More Than 700 Robberies Reported in Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, June 13 (Xinhua) -- More than 700 robberies were
reported in Costa Rica in the first five months this year, the
Judicial Investigation Organization (OIJ) said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The OIJ said that the January-May period saw the highest rate
of holdups. In May alone, there were 170 cases of robbery reported.
</P>
<P>
Banks and commercial outlets were the top targets of the armed
robberies. Up to now, nine banks across the country were assaulted
by armed bandits.
</P>
<P>
Among suspected groups are the juvenile delinquents known as
the "Chapulines" (Grass-hoppers), as well as motorcycle riders.
</P>
<P>
In May, the police busted one of the major criminal
bands. Local people urged the police to make more efforts in fight
against the brigands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
