<HEADLINE> Costa Rica's Tourism Revenue Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, June 13 (xinhua) -- Costa Rica earned 310 million
U.S. dollars from tourism during the January-April period, 15.2
percent up from the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The rise in the country's tourism revenue was attributed to the
increase in the number of foreign tourists, which soared by 16.29
percent, reported the Costa Rican Tourism Institute (ICT) on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Canada led the increase in the number of
foreign tourists to Costa Rica. Travelers from the United States
and Canada went up 21.29 percent and 17.29 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The ICT said that the income in hard currency from the tourism
sector will increase gradually because of intensified promotion
efforts. 
</P>
