<HEADLINE> Colombia's Oil Output Falls Short of Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Colombia produced
725,000 barrels of oil a day during the first five and a half
months of this year, the state-owned Empresa Colombiana de
Petroleos (Ecopetrol) oil company reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The figure is close to the record 740,000 barrels a day in
December 1997, but falls much short of the target of 1 million
barrels a day set for this year.
</P>
<P>
Ecopetrol's associated firms contributed an average of
601,700 barrels a day, while the direct Ecopetrol output was
119,600 barrels, said the report. 
</P>
