<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Oil Prices Keep Sliding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, June 13 (Xinhua) -- The price of the Venezuelan basket
of crudes and byproducts for export dropped 0.52 U.S. dollars a
barrel during the last week, down to 10.2 dollars a barrel.
</P>
<P>
The basket of seven crudes exported by the Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) lost 92 cents, closing the
same week at 11.82 dollars per barrel, according to figures
released by the Energy and Mines Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Economists attributed the continued slide in prices to high
inventories of oil warehoused by consumer countries and the
financial crisis in Southeast Asian countries. 
