<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Sewage Recycling Project Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- China has completed its largest
sewage recycling treatment project in Zibo, a city in east China's
Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The plant has passed provincial appraisal.
</P>
<P>
It can turn 30,000 tons of liquid waste into crystal-clear
purified water a day.
</P>
<P>
The Zibo Sewage Treatment Plant was built five years ago, with
140,000 tons of daily handling capacity.
</P>
<P>
The recycling project started in the second half of last year,
at a cost of 20 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Engineers at the plant say that the water can meet the national
standard of water for daily use, after undergoing second-degree
biochemical and fiber-tow filter treatment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
