<HEADLINE> TV Documentary on Jiang's US Visit to Be Broadcast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 14 (Xinhua) -- China's national TV station will
broadcast a documentary on June 19, featuring Chinese President
Jiang Zemin's visit to the United States last year.
</P>
<P>
The 60-minute documentary, produced by China Central Television
(CCTV), will cover the whole of Jiang's eight-day US tour.
</P>
<P>
During his state visit from October 26, 1997, President Jiang
participated in more than 40 events, delivered more than 30
speeches, and made extensive contact with the American people,
ushering in a new historical stage in the Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a documentary film on Jiang's visit, with the
title "Crossing the Pacific", will be shown throughout the country
beginning from June 15. The film is jointly produced by CCTV and
the Central Newsreels and Documentary Film Studio. 
</P>
</TEXT>
