<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 13 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Nelson Mandela Saturday encouraged the national soccer team to
fight on after they conceded a disastrous defeat to France on
Friday, local media reported.
</P>
<P>
Mandela told the team in a phone call that they should not
despair and continue their brave fight at the World Cup.
</P>
<P>
