them and had all the confidence in them. He wanted the team to
keep the flag flying high and that everybody in South Africa still
supported us," Radebe said.
</P>
<P>
South Africa went down 3-0 in their World Cup debut match
against France. They have to win both their remaining matches,
against Denmark and Saudi Arabia, to qualify for the second
round. 
