<HEADLINE> Belgium Forces Goalless Draw with Netherlands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAINT-DENIS, France, June 13 (Xinhua) -- Belgium forced a goalless
draw with soccer powerhouse in a Group E game here at the World Cup
finals on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Patrick Kluivert of AC Milan was sent off by referee Pierluigi
Collina in the 81st minute for elbowing a Belgian player.
</P>
<P>
But a more aggressive Dutch striking front pounded the defence line
of the Belgians frequently even after being reduced to 10 men,
bringing the total shots fired to 23 against Belgium's 6.
</P>
<P>
Belgian keeper Filip de Wilde became the hero for small European
nation, saving at least a dozen otherwisely deadly blasts from Jaap
Stam, Frank de Boer and second-half substitute Dennis Bergkamp.
</P>
<P>
Belgians Lorenzo Staelens and Eric Deflandre were shown yellow
cards in this hyped clash between the neighbours whose fans are
branded by French authorities as "high risk" at the Stade de France.
</P>
<P>
About 1,800 police were stationed in and near the stadium to
prevent possible flare-ups between the fans. 
</P>
