<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Expresses Concern About </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 13 (Xinhua)-- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
has expressed his concern about regional conflicts in the talks
with U.S. Ambassador to Uganda Mrs. Nancy Powell Saturday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
During the talks held at State House in Nakasero, they
discussed issues concerning the coming Burundi peace talks to be
held in Aarusha, Tanzania, and the fighiing between Ethiopia and
Eritrea over disputed border areas.
</P>
<P>
They expressed concern about the war between Ethiopia and
Eritrea and hoped that the two neighbors will resolve their
differences very soon.
</P>
<P>
