Organization of African Unity, which ended Wednesday in Burkina
Faso, by First Deputy Prime Minister Eriya Kategaya, Museveni
urged the two warring sides to seize the chance for the peaceful
resolution of their conflict within the framework laid out by the
facilitators.
</P>
<P>
On Burundi, Museveni welcomed some positive developments like
the release of the two former presidents, Ntibantugany and Bagaza
as well as parliament Speaker Ngendakumana and the imminent start
of the peace talks on Burundi.
</P>
<P>
He said that after talks begin in earnest and all sides
demonstrate a desire to engage in negotiations in good faith,
arrangements willbe made to convene a summit meeting to review
the question of sanctions imposed on Burundi.  
</P>
